1. *Počnite* od početka. (Start from the beginning.)
2. Da li *počinjete* da shvatate? (Are you starting to understand?)
3. *Počni* da radiš. (Start working.)
4. Moramo *početi* ranije. (We need to start earlier.)
5. *Počnite* da se krećete. (Start moving.)
6. Kada ćete *početi* da učite? (When will you start studying?)
7. *Počinjem* da se umaram. (I'm starting to get tired.)
8. *Počeli* smo da sprovodimo novu politiku. (We started implementing a new policy.)
9. Molim vas da *počnete* sa predstavljanjem. (Please start with the introduction.)
10. Nikada ne znate kada će nešto *početi* da se dešava. (You never know when something will start happening.)

(Note: *počnite* is the imperative form, *počinjete* and *počinjem* are the present tense forms, and *počni* and *početi* are the infinitive and past tense forms, respectively.) 

Translations:

1. Start from the beginning.
2. Are you starting to understand?
3. Start working.
4. We need to start earlier.
5. Start moving.
6. When will you start studying?
7. I'm starting to get tired.
8. We started implementing a new policy.
9. Please start with the introduction.
10. You never know when something will start happening.